race.comment: HOTIM ENGLISH (2) raced on the speed and lifted to score by 2.75L resuming from a spell over this trip. The top hoop sticks and he won his only second-up outing. Suitably placed and can go back-to-back. FRAWLEY (1) dug deep to score by 2.75L three runs back before filling minor placing at his last two starts. Has the pace to be in a prominent position and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. POLARISING (4) spiked her figures winning a 58 by 4.5L over a shorter sprint. The way she finished gives her a chance at 1200m. KISSING SUPIDO (3) ran below expectations in the same contest. He's better than that and can get into the finish if things go his way. STARSPANGLEDANCER (5) is in the right yard but may need another run.
